Overview

This repository documents a hands-on SQL Injection (SQLi) lab completed in a controlled and authorized environment. The objective was to understand how improper input validation and insecure database queries can allow an attacker to bypass authentication mechanisms.

The exercise demonstrates how HTTP requests can be analyzed using Burp Suite, how different request formats affect server behavior, and how vulnerable login functionality can be exploited when user input is not securely handled.

«Disclaimer: This project was performed in a legal training/laboratory environment for educational and defensive cybersecurity purposes only. The techniques discussed here should only be used on systems you own or have explicit permission to test.»

